<br>
So I drink Bombay sapphire gin &amp; tonics, love Tullamore Dew whiskey sours, like McCallans as my scotch or in my boilermaker with bass ale, good potato vodka for my vodka drinks, etc.<br>
<br>
/agree Kurley.  You know how to mix a gin &amp; tonic, nice to see that description, but I like more lime.<br>
<br>
I'm afraid this has rooted me out. .I'm a hedonistic elitist snob. . oh dear. ...what will become of me.<br>
<br>
*******************<br>
My all time favorite cocktail though is a Black Velvet Cocktail: <br>
<br>
take a frosty, tall, preferably fluted, beer glass.  The taller and narrower the glass, the better.  Ice tea glasses or pint beer glasses work in a pinch.<br>
<br>
put a spoonful of sugar and a splash of angostura bitters at the bottom.  Add 2/3rds glass best quality champagne you can lay your hands on (very cold).  Add 1/3rd glass guinness stout (room temperature). <br>
<br>
Be careful of the foaming, and don't ever even *think* of putting ice in this drink, gah.<br>
<br>
Oh, and if you find a bartender who you don't have to teach how to make one of these?  Marry him/her or something.  Wirtually no one knows how to make this drink, and some people will bring you the darnest things before they'll ask. <br>
<br>
